{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-page-js","path":"/config/main/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h2 id=\"description\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#description\" aria-label=\"description permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" fill=\"#fff\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Description</h2>\n<p>Main is what is left once the option and the commands have been extracted. Like with <code class=\"language-text\">options</code>, the <code class=\"language-text\">main</code> property is defined at the application level or for each command.</p>\n<h2 id=\"definition\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#definition\" aria-label=\"definition permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" fill=\"#fff\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Definition</h2>\n<p>The <code class=\"language-text\">main</code> property is declared as an object with the following properties:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">name</code> (string)<br>\nThe name of the main property.</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">required</code> (boolean || function)<br>\nWhether or not the value must always be present.</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">description</code> (string)<br>\nThe description of the main argument.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>As an alternative, a \"string\" can also be provided which will be converted to an object with the name property set to the original string value. Thus, the following declarations are equivalent:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token function\">shell</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  main<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'input'</span>  \n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// is equivalent to</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">shell</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  main<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    name<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'input'</span> \n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> \n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>The extracted value is an array.</p>\n<p>If <a href=\"https://github.com/adaltas/node-shell/blob/master/samples/main_empty.js\">no main arguments</a> is defined in the CLI commands, then the array is empty.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token function\">require</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'should'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">require</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'shell'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  main<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'input'</span> \n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">parse</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>should<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">eql</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  input<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"using-code-classlanguage-textrequiredcode-as-a-function\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#using-code-classlanguage-textrequiredcode-as-a-function\" aria-label=\"using code classlanguage textrequiredcode as a function permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" fill=\"#fff\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Using <code class=\"language-text\">required</code> as a function</h2>\n<p>When <code class=\"language-text\">required</code> is a function, the first argument is an object with the following properties:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">config</code><br>\nThe configuration associated with the command or the full configuration is no command is used.</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">command</code>\nThe current command name, use <code class=\"language-text\">config.command</code> to acess the full command as an array.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"examples\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#examples\" aria-label=\"examples permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" fill=\"#fff\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Examples</h2>\n<h2 id=\"application-level-definition\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#application-level-definition\" aria-label=\"application level definition permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" fill=\"#fff\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Application level definition</h2>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token function\">require</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"shell\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  main<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"leftover\"</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>The above is the equivalent of declaring options as an array like:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token function\">require</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"shell\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  main<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    name<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"leftover\"</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Usage of the \"main\" parameter is now: <code class=\"language-text\">myapp [leftover]</code>.</p>\n<h2 id=\"command-level-definition\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#command-level-definition\" aria-label=\"command level definition permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" fill=\"#fff\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Command level definition</h2>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token function\">require</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"shell\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  commands<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    name<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'server'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    commands<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      name<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'start'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n      main<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'leftover'</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Usage of the \"main\" parameter is now: <code class=\"language-text\">myapp server start [leftover]</code>.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Main parameter usage","keywords":["shell","node.js","cli","usage","main"],"description":"How to use main parameter."},"fields":{"edit_url":"https://github.com/adaltas/node-shell/edit/master/content/config/main.md","slug":"/config/main/"},"headings":[{"value":"Description","depth":2,"id":"description"},{"value":"Definition","depth":2,"id":"definition"},{"value":"Using <code class=\"language-text\">required</code> as a function","depth":2,"id":"using-code-classlanguage-textrequiredcode-as-a-function"},{"value":"Examples","depth":2,"id":"examples"},{"value":"Application level definition","depth":2,"id":"application-level-definition"},{"value":"Command level definition","depth":2,"id":"command-level-definition"}]}},"pageContext":{}},"staticQueryHashes":["1387919533","63159454"]}